      • getListHeight

        public int getListHeight(Context context,
                         java.util.List<SliceItem> listItems)
        Expects the provided list of items to be filtered (i.e. only things that can be turned into GridContent or RowContent) and in order (i.e. first item could be a header).
        Returns:
        the total height of all the rows contained in the provided list.

      • getItemsForNonScrollingList

        @NonNull
public java.util.List<SliceItem> getItemsForNonScrollingList(int height)
        Returns a list of items that can be displayed in the provided height. If this list has a getSeeMoreItem() this will be returned in the list if appropriate.
        Parameters:
        height - the height to restrict the items, -1 to use default sizings for non-scrolling templates.
        Returns:
        the list of items that can be displayed in the provided height.

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
